class Solution {
    public int[] twoSum(int[] numbers, int target) {
        int len = numbers.length;
        int start=0, end=len-1;

        while(start<end){
            int sumOfNum = numbers[start]+numbers[end];
            if(sumOfNum == target){
                return new int[]{start+1,end+1};
            }else if(sumOfNum < target){
                start++;
            }else{
                end--;
            }
        }
        return new int[]{0,0};
    }
}


Approach : 

Start moving from left and right.
Check the sum, if sum is greater than target -> r--
               if sum is less than target -> l--

To reduce the sum, move the right pointer to the left
To increase the sum, move the left pointer to the right
